OL,6,F"He told her that her wrist was broken
OL,7,Fand she had bruising to her eyes and
OL,8,Fshoulder and she was lay on the bed.
OL,9,FMary told the defendant that Suzanne
OL,10,Fneeded to go to hospital, but he told
OL,11,Fhis grandmother that Suzanne said she
OL,12,Fdid not want to go to hospital at that
OL,13,Fstage and would go in the morning."
OL,15,FMrs Galvin asked to speak to her
OL,16,Fdaughter and could hear her breathing
OL,17,F"erratically", jurors were told. She
OL,18,Ftried to persuade Ball to call an
OL,19,Fambulance, but he said he had "no
OL,20,Fcredit", so she called 999 herself.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
