OL,3,CSon's trainers left 'pattern' on mum's
OL,4,Cface as he stamped on her head
OL,6,FBall pleaded guilty to manslaughter
OL,7,Fbased on the partial defence of
OL,8,Fdiminished responsibility. He denied
OL,9,Fmurder and did not give evidence at
OL,10,Fhis trial, but jurors found him
OL,11,Funanimously guilty. He will be
OL,12,Fsentenced on 1 November.
OL,14,FAddressing the jury, Judge Martin
OL,15,FWalsh said: "The sentence is fixed by
OL,16,Flaw as life imprisonment, I have to
OL,17,Fdetermine the mandatory minimum term
OL,18,Fand I will hear arguments about that
OL,19,Fnext time."
